{{Infobox software | name = Defraggler | logo = [[File:Defraggler icon.png|64px]] | screenshot = [[File:Defragglerscreen.png|300px]] | caption = Defraggler defragmenting in [[Windows 7]] | developer = [[Piriform (company)|Piriform]] | released = {{Start date and age|2008|8|18}}<ref name="File Hippo">{{Cite web | title = Download Defraggler | url = http://www.filehippo.com/download_defraggler/tech/453/ | publisher = FileHippo | accessdate = June 23, 2009 }}</ref> | latest_release_version = 2.08.373 | latest_release_date = {{Start date and age|2011|11|14}} | operating system = [[Windows XP]] and later | platform = [[IA-32]] and [[x64]] | language = English, Albanian, Arabic, Bosanski, Deutsch, Dutch, Espanol (Spanish), French, Greek, Hebrew, Italiano (Italian), Japanese, Magyar, Norwegian, PortuguÃªs (Portuguese), PortuguÃªs do Brasil (Brazilian Portuguese), Romana (Romanian), Russian, Suomi (Finnish), Svenska (Swedish) and Ukrainian<ref name="lang">{{cite web|title=Multi-lingual support|url=http://www.piriform.com/defraggler/features/multi-lingual-support|work=Defraggler - Features|publisher=Piriform|accessdate=1 July 2011}}</ref> | size = 3.10 [[Megabyte|MB]] | genre = [[Defragmentation software]] | license = [[Freemium]] | website = {{URL|www.piriform.com/defraggler}} }} '''Defraggler''', developed by [[Piriform (company)|Piriform]], is a free [[donationware]] [[defragmentation]] utility, which notably allows users to defragment individual files on their computer system. Defraggler runs on [[Microsoft Windows]]; it has support for all versions since [[Windows XP]]. It includes support for both IA-32 and x64 versions of these operating systems.<ref name="File Hippo" />
== Overview == Defraggler defragment individual files, groups of files (in a folder) or an entire [[Disk partitioning|disk partition]], either by user's command or automatically on a schedule. It supports [[File Allocation Table#FAT32|FAT32]], [[NTFS]], and [[exFAT]].<ref>{{cite web|title=System requirements|url=http://www.piriform.com/docs/defraggler/introducing-defraggler/system-requirements|work=Defraggler documentation|publisher=Piriform|accessdate=22 July 2011}}</ref> It can also be installed as [[portable application]] on a [[USB flash drive]]. Defragmenting [[RAID]] disks are also supported, although no details are supplied.<ref>{{cite web|title=What it can and can't do|url=http://www.piriform.com/docs/defraggler/introducing-defraggler/what-it-can-and-can%27t-do|work=Defraggler documentation|publisher=Piriform|accessdate=22 July 2011}}</ref>
Defraggler was given a 5/5 star rating from [[Softpedia]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Piriform Defraggler - Keeping Those Drives Spinning|url=http://www.softpedia.com/reviews/windows/Defraggler--Review-91537.shtml|first=Daniela|last=Olariu|publisher=SoftNews NET SRL|work=Softpedia|date=August 6, 2008|accessdate=June 5, 2011}}</ref> In [[Lifehacker]]'s Hive Five for Best Disk Defragmenter, Defraggler received first place.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Best Disk Defragmenter: Defraggler |url=http://lifehacker.com/5350497/best-disk-defragmenter-defraggler|first=Jason|last=Fitzpatrick|publisher=Gawker Media|work=Life Hacker|date=September 1, 2009|accessdate=May 11, 2010}}</ref>
